Text:
Wow! So this is a spirit! It's so fluffy!
Fluffy-wuffy!
Urgh! Argh, ugh!!!

Your name's Nuru? Okay, from now on you're my
sidekick!
S-Somebody help me... Urrrgh...
He's been crushed... Shouldn't we do something?

Eh, I'm sure it's fine. At least this way all her
damage focused on one target. You don't want her
bugging you while you try to study, do you?

Good point... In that case, let's continue. If you
would be so kind, Professor Zeta?

Feels kinda weird having you call me that... All I
did was tell you how to use the camera.

Heehee, oh, what's the harm? Now, come on, hurry up
and teach me about filters.

Alright, alright. So, these two photos were taken in
the same place at the same time, but when you apply
a filter...

Wow... They look completely different. I didn't know
the camera could do that.

There's also a timer function. It's helpful for when
you want to take group photos.
...Why the camera study session?

Well, is this not the Photography Club? I need to
know more about cameras and photos.

That's only the name... All I did was take over a
club with no one in it...

So, yes, we do intend to use this club as a front.
We can't go around fighting evil spirits and
collecting Bones openly, after all.

But that's no reason for us to totally ignore the
club's outward appearance. Causing trouble and a
lack of members weren't the only reason you got
recommended for disbandment, right?
Well...

You haven't been doing any of the activities listed
on the club description. That's why the student
council came after you so strongly... Am I wrong?

That's why we need to make sure to also do things
that fall within the club description. Speaking of,
can I take a photo of you?
...No need for that...
Huh?

You don't have to worry...about me... In return...
you can do whatever you want with the club...
S-Sure...

(She's definitely keeping her distance... Did us
joining the club bother her that much?)
Urgh... Rrrrgh... Hnnf!
Ah! He got away!

*pant, gasp*... You all seem to be having trouble
gelling.
You okay there, Nuru?

I-I'm fine...! More importantly, find some way to
loosen up around each other for the battles ahead!

Since you're all in this together, how about
becoming friends? Go hang out around town
and get to know each other.

Good idea... Let's adjourn the club meeting here for
today and go have some fun like Nuru suggested.

You three go ahead... I want to focus on my
research...

You're coming, too! Sitting too much will rot your
brain!

Funny coming from someone with no brain to speak
of... Agh...don't drag me...

This is one time where that bullheadedness of hers
comes in handy. Shall we be off?
Yes, let's. How about you, Nuru?

I'll hold down the fort. Wouldn't want to intrude on
these precious days of youth.

Precious days of youth...? Well, whatever.
We'll be back later.
Crowds...bother me...
You okay? Make sure you don't get lost.
I'll keep an eye on her.

So, where're we going and what're we doing? An old
standby like karaoke seems good for a time like this.

What do you sing, Alpha? Pop music, like stuff by
Epsilon?

Um... So karaoke is a place where you go to sing
something?
Huh? Um, yeah, basically.

Who are we singing for? And, won't we need to
practice together first?

Ahaha, that's not what karaoke is at all. It's more
like passing the mic around singing in a small room.
And the only audience is us.

O-Oh, right... Sorry, it's just I've never done
karaoke before...

Well, then now you really need to experience it.
Okay, today we're doing karaoke!

Don't just pick for everybody! I wanna go bowling!
Just singing is boring!
It's not boring. You're singing and listening, too.

Well, I don't wanna just sit! Moving around is more
fun!
Those two never change...
...Whew.
Is this all too much for you, Eta?
I wouldn't call it too much, butâ€”
...I don't know.
Huh...?
Hey, Alpha, Eta! C'mon, we're going bowling!

Not so fast. You guys would much rather do karaoke
today, right?
Bowling!!!
Karaoke!!!

Good grief... Fine, we'll do karaoke and then go
bowling. Does that work for you, Eta?
...I guess.
